caption: Lasagna and calamari were delicious!

This place is great! They wear gloves they have masks, hand sanitizer at entrance and in bathrooms. The food is fresh the staff is friendly and there is limoncello. A wonderful trattoria! Authentic, Venetian owned and operated. Small business.

We had an amazing experience! Not only was the atmosphere beyond our expectations the service was impeccable. All of our dishes were made to perfection. Try this place you won’t regret it. The friendly and professional staff made our experience go from great to incredible. Thank you we will be back!
Excellent

We arrived at this place for lunch. my friend recommended this place.  Well, it was very successful. The staff members welcomed us with a smile and we felt good. The meal was fresh and delicious. We had a great time and we will definitely return to this restaurant. We recommend this place to all.
If you are looking for authentic Italian food. You are coming to the right place.
I just enjoy their dishes. I always get awesome customer service here. The place is clean and the employees are always super nice. I highly recommend this place.
Nice staff. Free dessert

Wow this place was amazing!!  The atmosphere and service was top notch.  I had mussels, veal Marsala , and an espresso.  I would recommend this place for anyone looking for authentic Italian good.  I felt like I was in Italy.
Delicous! Great spot for lunch!
We found this quiet place on our first night in DC. The atmosphere was great and the food was amazing. It was not the cheapest place but you get what you pay for.
Wow. This place is great! Ambience, service, and food.

From the moment  you come to this place  the stuff gives you a comfortable feeling. Very friendly stuff, it is a friendly place to to go out with friends and colleagues or with your date. Excellent  food, qualified  chef, comfortable  pay and professional  service. Warmly recommended.
Great mom and pop restaurant.  Highly recommended.  Tiramisu was delicious

This place is marvelous! Great food and even better service. The staff was really attentive and fast. When I made the reservation online, I noted that it was our anniversary. They surprised my wife and I with some tiramisu after our meal! It was so nice. They woman said she hoped our anniversary was as sweet as their tiramisu! Such a nice and thoughtful act.  We had the tiramisu, Garlic Bread with Gorgonzola Cheese, Spaghetti Carbonara, and Rigatoni con Salciccia. I recommend each of those! Great portions and delicious. The tiramisu was the best I’ve had. The garlic bread was delicious. The carbonara was top notch. The rigatoni has the perfect kick of spiciness. This will definitely be my family’s Italian place going forward.

My wife and I visited DC and celebrated our first anniversary. We found this hidden gem of a restaurant and we would definitely return if we come back to town. The food is delicious. The prices are reasonable. Best of all, the service was spectacular... our server, Gallina was the best!! If you want an authentic Italian meal and you truly want to feel at home... try this place. You will absolutely love the entire experience!!

Charming garden level restaurant reached by a short staircase down. Pleasant kitchen aromas of garlic and bread upon entering. A special effort was made to accommodate a party of three with no reservation. Food (linguini and seafood sampler in garlic, wine sauce) was thought delicious by one and boring by another in the party of three. It was VERY pricey with no accompanying side dishes except plain bread and olive oil. Service was prompt but cold almost to the point of unfriendliness.
A real taste of Italy 🇮🇹 in DC!
Good little restraunt. Service was excellent.
We love this restaurant.  The food is fantastic and the atmosphere is perfect.
Delicious cuisine

I eat in this place  a lot! This is my favorite spot to have a bite.  I visit this spot frequently. The cooking is excellent, the team is friendly and the prices are fair. I like being in this place over a decent dinner.
delicious meal!  we came back 2 years later..
What a beautiful hidden place. Loved it.

What a wonderful little gem hidden away in downtown DC.  Reasonably priced for lunch any time and perfect for special occasions.  The agnolotti porcini was so rich and delicious.  The bread was fresh and crusty.  Patricia provided excellent service.  A haven on a cold, rainy winter day.
Awesome place
A great classy restaurant with spectacular food. Average cost $40 per head with desert and wine. The teramisu is to die for.
Chicken Parmesan was great!!
Cute resturant. Great food. Quiet not loud.
A very nice and quaint restaurant. Amazing food and great service. One of the best Italian restaurants I’ve ever been to.
Excellent service, good food
Ambiance, food and service; all excellent. It was an enjoyable experience.

(Translated by Google) Small place, cozy. Very good service. We ordered a carpaccio, fish, salad, pasta and dessert ... and everything was delicious. Highly recommended  (Original) Lugar pequeño, acogedor. Muy buen servicio. Pedimos un carpaccio,pescados, ensalada, pasta y postre... y todo fue delicioso. Muy recomendable.
Excellent food and service! Chicken parmesan is tender and delicious. Definitely worth the short walk from Dupont Circle station.

(Translated by Google) A lovely Italian with a homely atmosphere. Because there is a shop under the stairs, if you think about it, it may pass by? Each person will be attached to the table.  We ordered cream risotto of lasagna, vongole, porcini & mushroom but they are all delicious! Five adults and one toddler share it.  Don't overeat your first bread! Both wine and dessert Tiramisu were delicious.  The moment I left the shop, I thought about when I would come next ^ _ ^  Good conversation with delicious rice and wine, it was a really great time! Thank you for bringing me.  It seems better to make a reservation on Fridays and weekends. Risotto absolutely eat ~!  (Original) 家庭的な雰囲気の素敵なイタリアン。 階段下にお店があるので考えごとをしてると通り過ぎてしまうかも？ テーブルに各担当が付いてくれます。  ラザニア、ボンゴレ、ポルチーニ&マッシュルームのクリームリゾット頼んだけれどどれも美味しい！ 大人五人と幼児一人でシェアしました。  最初のパンは食べすぎないで！ ワインもデザートのティラミスも美味しかったです。  お店を出た瞬間に次にいつ来ようかと思ったくらいです^_^  美味しいご飯とワインに楽しい会話、本当にとても楽しい時間でした！ 連れてきて頂いて感謝。  金曜や週末は予約をされた方がよいみたいです。 リゾットは絶対に食べて〜！
Friendly place
We enjoyed our gathering with colleagues. Staff are very friendly and have good sense of humor.
Very charming restaurant just off the beaten path in DC. The staff is Italian so it's an authentic experience!
(Translated by Google) Fantastic! Cozy place with excellent cuisine, I recommend it !! Elena  (Original) Fantastico! Locale accogliente, con cucina eccellente,  lo consiglio!! Elena
Cozy little spot in a great location. The clam sause linguini was very good.
Nice cozy delicious Italian restaurant. The food was good, the staff was pleasant except the restaurant was extremely small.
Quaint and full of character - food was great!

One of the best meals I've had in DC! The calamari was some of the best I've ever had, lightly breaded and perfectly fried. Also came with some slices of fried zucchini which was a nice touch. The cheesy gorgonzola bread was fantastic as well. Most of our party ordered pasta and found the serving sizes to be perfect - not too much but still very filling. All of their pasta is homemade and it shows! I am definitely planning to come back and would highly recommend anyone try this restaurant.
So good. No crowd on a Saturday night: Not overpriced and very tasty! Great service.

Extremely hot inside, the place was 79 F degree,  really bad air conditioner, it was around 0800 pm. My food was very salty and the price for the size of the meal was very high. My family and I will not go back. The service was nothing special.  This was my opinion!!!
It is a small little Italian joint that has authentic amazing food!
Fun, old-school atmosphere, friendly service, and terrific food. The modest exterior might give you pause, but go on in, it’s special.

I have relatives in town. I had to been to Giovanni's previously and it was wonderful.  It's tucked away in the lower level of a row house.  It has an authentic feel, which is complimented by delicious cuisine and attentive staff.
Food is excellent. Service very friendly. Atmosphere is quaint and cute.  Small, friendly feeling.  Very nice place to have a meal.
OK food, average atmosphere

It’s a small, “hole in the wall” type place that may easily be passed up but let me tell you - AMAZING!! I had the carbonara and my boyfriend had the baked ziti dish and we were both blown away by how good the meal was! We’re already talking about our next trip.
Good meal, nice place
Excellent dinner at this quaint Italian restaurant near DuPont Circle.  Great service and friendly staff.
Always a treat. Traditional favorites and some tasty appetizers as great looking and tasty entrees. Can't miss.
The food was delicious and the place was cozy

A family dinner at a local restaurant where you feel like family. Great food and great service. All courses nicely paced. Nothing was rushed. Nice aesthetics. If we weren't just visiting DC, we would make Trattu a regular dinner stop. We will be back.
Delicious food in a very warm environment. Very considerate staff, too.
Cute little hole in the wall restaurant in Dupont Circle. Food was delicious.
Good food.  Good atmosphere.

(Translated by Google) Delicious food, lasagna, pasta carbonara and frutti di mari was very rich, as well as desserts and red wine.  (Original) Deliciosa comida, la lasaña, la pasta carbonara y frutti di mari estuvo muy rico, al igual que los postres y el vino tinto.
Both times we've eaten here the food and service have been excellent!
(Translated by Google) Very good Italian restaurant  (Original) Muy buen restaurante italiano
Excellent food and service in a charming setting.

We had wonderful service and great eats at Giovanni's Tarttu! I called ahead of time to reserve a table for my boyfriend's 21st birthday. When we arrived the hostess knew right who we were and wished my boyfriend a happy birthday. After the delicious dinner she came back out with tiramisu with a candle on top. I wasn't expecting the service that we received, it was a great experience. We have plans to visit again soon.
Great little find for authentic Italian.
(Translated by Google) A good Italian restaurant. Pasta cooked well, average prices of the place  (Original) Un buon ristorante italiano. Pasta cotta bene, prezzi nella media del posto
We went here as a large group and everything was delicious, the servers were very helpful and friendly! I'd love to go back!

(Translated by Google) The place is small but very cozy, there is a small room where all the tables are, it is an Italian restaurant, it is set up with great taste and it is very good. The staff are very friendly and even speak Spanish. The food is very good and very well presented. I really liked this restaurant.  (Original) El sitio es pequeñito pero muy acogedor, hay un pequeño saloncito donde  están todas las mesas, se trata de un restaurante italiano, está montado con mucho gusto y se está muy bien. El personal es muy amable e incluso hablan español. La comida está muy buena y muy bien presentada. Me ha gustado mucho este restaurante.
Loved the pasta trio, especially the veal tortellini. The mixed green salad was a nice starter, a little old school with red radish slice.
Excellent! Same place Lovely Wife and I used to go here years ago. Nice to see Giovanni took it back to the lovely  romantic place we remember.  I highly recommend this for both food and experience.
The food was decent, but the place is musty and has a smell that needs to be addressed.
Beautiful interior inside. Very cozy. Great food too.
Authentic Italian Foood. Best of DC!
Tiramisu is fantastic!
Nice off the beaten path and good service
Feels like homemade meals!
Small intimate setting. A variety of pasta and fish dishes. Entrees we're about $18 to $29.
The Gnocchi with pesto sauce was amazing!  So fresh and delicious! The service was attentive and ambiance was nice!  Great neighborhood gem!
(Translated by Google) Good food and kind service!  (Original) Comida boa e atendimento gentil!

Walked in excited for a great meal. Asked where the restroom was server showed me the way. You look at the kitchen and make a right to the men's room. Inside was dry and clean but smelled like raw sewage. So not sure where the problem was but to smell like that next to the kitchen made me walk out immediately.
Very delicious food and customer service was great as well
Very efficient and friendly staff. Good food.
The food was ok, I think they really could have stepped it up a notch or two for those prices. It felt more like a diner than a nice restaurant

My wife and I are in town celebrating our 3 year anniversary and we had quite the experience. The food was fantastic and fresh but we had terrible service (at first). One of the young ladies spent 15 minutes chatting away with "friends" while my wife and I sat there not being waited on. She offered the other table fresh Parmesan and cracked pepper as a topping on their entrees but never offered us any. However, two other waitresses saw that we were not being attended to and practically took over for the first waitress. The original waitress would only occasionally stop by (in between conversation) to just fill up our waters but the others would come by on a routine basis to make sure we were ok. At the end of the night, we faced a conundrum: we want to leave a tip but we do not want the first waitress to pick it up. We asked to speak with a manager about the matter and she waived the whole meal. Wow! Well, I couldn't leave without anything, so I walked to the nearest ATM and withdrew money for a tip and gave the tip money to the other two waitresses. I also gave the manager (who also is the owner's wife) some cash for our meals since it was not her fault. FOOD WAS EXCELLENT AND OVERALL THE WAITING WAS GREAT!

The food was good.  However, the place has seen better days.  There was a dank moldy smell in the dining room on the cold night we dined.  This is probably due to the place being in the basement. I think they need to  renovate and replace the carpet either with new carpet or wood flooring. I give the food 4 stars, but one star for the atmosphere.  I wouldn't come back unless it's a nice day, and I can sit outside.
Very tasty cousine, couzy atmosphere, and freindly personal

Came here with a party of 12. Great service and the apps tasted great until a maggot crawled out of my friends food.  What!!!! There is a first time for everything. Waiter came over killed it with a napkin. We also tried to brush it off but and eat our entrées but around  30 mintues later another one was lurking on the table. GROSS!  We left.
Wonderful people, delicious food and great drinks. The garlic bread is awesome and the chicken parmesan and marsala are both great! Enjoy!

The place is very small but handled a couple tables of six with no problem. The food was ok but not my favorite style of Italian and two dishes, one appetizer and three half-glasses of wine costing over $80 (plus a tip) it was a disappointment for me. It got good ratings from online sites  so it's your choice.... I won't go back though.
Great food and service, would recommend.
Ambiance is super cozy and romantic. Food is really, really great and authentic. You can tell they use fresh ingredients. It's a bit on the pricier end but worth the combination of food and ambiance.

The best Italian restaurant I've ever been to up to now. I was recommended to try Veal Mccoy (veal means meat from a calf - a young cow) and couldn't be more satisfied. It was so tender and the wine sauce was really tasty. Most of my people in the group enjoyed their meal too so my guess is that the chef here is really doing his good job. Highly recommended!  It is expensive (to me), though :<  Mon, 02/27/2017 - Washington D.C.

Nice cozy italian joint with solid food. It's pretty easy to walk right by this place! The decor isn't as gaudy as others may have indicated. Muscles were good, definitely would recommend. The gnocchi was very good as well. Went with several friends and we liked it enough to get dessert! Would go back. Not too noisy, well lit - wouldnt make a bad date night spot.
Great authentic Italian place.  Delicious Gnocchi.
Awesome experience. Staff was superb, food was delicious. Highly recommended. I proposed to my now wife here, as did my father to my mother, and with the same ring. I'm glad they are still around.
Great Italian food

It's a very cute space - the dining area is large and open, but decor and atmosphere is like being in someone's dining room. The service was great -- staff very attentive and happy to make suggestions and chat.
So wonderful.  The agnalotti was large but who cares!?  Taste was wonderful!
The employees are very nice, the food is OK, I was expecting better food because of the price
Good food. But a little bit expensive
Wonderful service and homemade traditional Italian food. A required dining stop every time I'm in town.
A surprise tucked away. Very good

As others have mentioned, this is a hole in the wall place serving good Italian food. This place is easy to miss if you don't pay attention, and then you have to step down to get to the restaurant.  It is a tiny place compared to other restaurants in the neighborhood and generally more than half the tables are occupied.  They have a decent selection of real Italian dishes. The dishes here are not overly cheesy nor buttery - and pasta is cooked perfectly - al dente!  I generally get the rigatoni with Italian sausage, or the linguine with mussels, or the fettuccini.  They do have a good selection of dessert but I never have any place in my stomach for it as the main dish is generous enough for my appetite!  Service is good too and that goes well with the food :)  Nice little gem in the area :)
Excellent attention to the 18 people I brought, and that is not usually the case.  It was a delight.  The food was excellent!  We were having such fun, trying all the dishes...great place!

Had the agnolotti di casa mia and mozzarella fritti alla gondogliera. The "agnolotti" were actually large raviolis made with thick dough in a heavy sauce, whereas true agnoltti are a small pocket in a very simple broth or butter sauce. Was disappointed there. The fried mozzarella was like any fried food: makes you happy, then makes you question your life choices.  You must check out their vintage website though!

Unassuming little place in the basement unit of a townhouse down quiet Jefferson Street. Food is surprisingly spot-on; pasta with bolognese is delicious and perfectly al dente. Decor is dated. Service is pleasant and attentive. Prices aren't cheap.

Very small restaurant and doesn't look like much but the food is really good and the service isn't bad. You do need to make a reservation for most nights though as there isn't very much seating at all.
